subject: Re: [junit] My First mail
msgSnippet: ... Please give an example of some tests that you would want to generate automatically and tell us what you would get if you could do that. Thanks, Ron
messageBody:
On Wednesday, January 7, 2004, at 11:54:42 PM, chandana S wrote:

> 1. I just want to know a few test case generators that can generate the test cases automatically for
> Java programs. If possible I want the list of Open sources as well.

> 2. Can we generate the test cases automatically using JUnit. I think at least for the first time we are
> supposed to write the first set of test cases manually. I know to write the test cases manually but how
> can we generate the test cases automatically from the first set of manual ones?

Please give an example of some tests that you would want to generate
automatically and tell us what you would get if you could do that.

Thanks,

Ron Jeffries
www.XProgramming.com
To be on the wire is life. The rest is waiting. --Karl Wallenda
